observationText: The SW620 cell line was derived from a lymph node metastasis of the same colorectal carcinoma patient as the SW480 cell line. Both cell lines share the TP53 mutations c.925C>T (p.P309S) and c.818G>A (p.R273H). SW620 exhibits high levels of potentially bisected complex or hybrid N-glycan structures compared to non-metastatic cell lines, which may be related to its metastatic origin.
